</marc:datafield>
    <marc:datafield ind1=" " ind2=" " tag="500">
  <marc:subfield code="a">Decoration:  Manicules used by the scribe to flag missing text and indicate where it should be inserted (p. 2).</marc:subfield>
</marc:datafield>
    <marc:datafield ind1=" " ind2=" " tag="500">
  <marc:subfield code="a">Watermarks:  Similar to Churchill 214, Arms of England of Van der Ley and Honig, 1733, but with intials LVG below (p. i); similar to countermark of Churchil 214, crowned GR (p. v).</marc:subfield>
</marc:datafield>
    <marc:datafield ind1=" " ind2=" " tag="500">
  <marc:subfield code="a">Binding:  Contemporary (18th-century) quarter calf with marbled boards (Weinberger); upper cover and first three leaves detached; lower cover nearly detached.</marc:subfield>
</marc:datafield>
    <marc:datafield ind1=" " ind2=" " tag="500">
  <marc:subfield code="a">Origin: Written in Chennai (called Madraspatam in the manuscript) in 1728 (title page, p. vii).</marc:subfield>
